The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 28 April is 41,858 (4,844.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 23 April, there were 125 new confirmed cases (14.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 16 April, there were 141 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 11% (16 fewer cases).
